# Line-ending and binary handling for a cross-platform repo (developed
# on Windows, tested on Linux CI). The committed tree is already all
# LF; this locks that in so a contributor whose Git has core.autocrlf
# off can't land CRLF and create diff noise. Working-tree checkout
# stays native unless a rule below pins it.
* text=auto

# Bash scripts must stay LF in the working tree too: CRLF breaks the
# shebang and parser on the Linux runners.
*.sh text eol=lf

# Binary assets: never diff, never normalize line endings.
*.png binary
